We concur: Bridgewater, P.J., Quinn-Brintnall, J.
[fn1] Miranda v. Arizona, 384 U.S. 436, 86 S. Ct. 1602. 16 L. Ed. 2d 694 (1966).
[fn2] "Segregation" is otherwise known as "inmate isolation," where the inmate has no contact with other inmates. The slang phrase Moinette uses is "the hole."
[fn3] We further note that, even if the trial court had found, which it did not, that the escorting correction officer had told Moinette he would return to the general inmate population without consequence for admitting to the assault, this officer was not one of the interrogating officers and he did not testify at the CrR 3.5 hearing.
